goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This will help identify airports with the highest number of bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes at those airports.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This will help identify the most vulnerable aircrafts and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes on those aircrafts.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?
goals.rationale: This will help identify the most common wildlife species involved in bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes involving those species.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?
goals.rationale: This will help identify the phases of flight with the highest number of bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes during those phases.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data['Airport_Name'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport Name')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Aircraft_Make_Model'] = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].astype('category')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().head(20).plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?')
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Wildlife_Species'] = pd.Categorical(data['Wildlife_Species'])
    data['Wildlife_Species'] = data['Wildlife_Species'].cat.codes
    species_counts = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_counts.index = pd.Categorical.from_codes(species_counts.index, data['Wildlife_Species'].cat.categories)
    species_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Flight_Date')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(integer=True))
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.plot(data['Time_of_day'].value_counts().sort_index())
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by time of day?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
